    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Notice how the bounces get smaller and smaller!\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 🎯 Challenges\n",
        "\n",
        "### 🌟 Easy Challenges\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Change Gravity**: Make gravity stronger (1.0) or weaker (0.25)\n",
        "2. **Modify Friction**: Make balls bouncier (0.95) or less bouncy (0.7)\n",
        "3. **Add More Colors**: Create new color options\n",
        "\n",
        "### 🌟🌟 Medium Challenges\n",
        "\n",
        "4. **Add Ball Collisions**: Make balls bounce off each other\n",
        "5. **Size Matters**: Make smaller balls bounce higher than large ones\n",
        "6. **Wind Effect**: Add horizontal force to simulate wind\n",
        "\n",
        "### 🌟🌟🌟 Hard Challenges\n",
        "\n",
        "7. **Trail Effect**: Show the path balls have traveled\n",
        "8. **Energy Display**: Show total energy in the system\n",
        "9. **Sticky Floor**: Make balls stick after bouncing a few times\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 💡 Code Variations to Try\n",
        "\n",
        "### Different Ball Behaviors\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "# Super bouncy ball\n",
        "FRICTION = 1.0\n",
        "MIN_BOUNCE_VELOCITY = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "# Heavy ball (less bouncy)\n",
        "FRICTION = 0.6\n",
        "GRAVITY = 0.8\n",
        "\n",
        "# Moon physics\n",
        "GRAVITY = 0.1\n",
        "FRICTION = 0.95\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### Random Spawn Positions\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "# In main(), instead of clicking, spawn balls automatically\n",
        "import time\n",
        "\n",
        "last_spawn_time = time.time()\n",
        "\n",
        "# In game loop:\n",
        "current_time = time.time()\n",
        "if current_time - last_spawn_time > 0.5:  # Every 0.5 seconds\n",
        "    x = random.randint(50, WINDOW_WIDTH - 50)\n",
        "    y = 50\n",
        "    radius = random.randint(15, 40)\n",
        "    color = random.choice(COLORS)\n",
        "    balls.append(Ball(x, y, radius, color))\n",
        "    last_spawn_time = current_time\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 📚 Key Terms to Remember\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Velocity**: Speed and direction of movement\n",
        "- **Acceleration**: Rate of change of velocity (gravity is constant acceleration)\n",
        "- **Gravity**: Downward acceleration (makes things fall)\n",
        "- **Friction/Restitution**: Energy loss during collisions\n",
        "- **Vector**: A quantity with both magnitude (size) and direction\n",
        "- **Frame**: One update cycle of the game (60 FPS = 60 updates/second)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 🔬 Physics Fun Facts\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-consider}\n",
        "## 🤔 Real World Physics\n",
        "\n",
        "**Did you know?**\n",
        "\n",
        "- On Earth, gravity accelerates objects at 9.8 m/s² (about 32 ft/s²)\n",
        "- On the Moon, gravity is only 1.62 m/s² (about 1/6 of Earth's)\n",
        "- A real tennis ball has a coefficient of restitution around 0.75\n",
        "- No ball bounces perfectly (friction = 1.0) due to energy loss to heat and sound!\n",
        "\n",
        "In our game, 1 pixel/frame² is like our unit of \"game gravity\". Try different values to simulate different planets!\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 💡 Tips for Better Physics Games\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Keep Frame Rate Consistent**: Use `clock.tick(FPS)` to ensure smooth physics\n",
        "2. **Start with Simple Physics**: Get basic movement working before adding complexity\n",
        "3. **Use Small Gravity Values**: Large values make movement look unrealistic\n",
        "4. **Test Edge Cases**: What happens with very large velocities? Very small balls?\n",
        "5. **Visual Feedback**: The velocity vectors help debug physics issues\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 🏁 Wrapping Up\n",
        "\n",
        "Amazing work! You've created a physics simulation with realistic bouncing, gravity, and friction. You now understand how games create realistic movement!\n",
        "\n",
        "### What You Accomplished\n",
        "\n",
        "✅ Implemented velocity and acceleration  \n",
        "✅ Created gravity simulation  \n",
        "✅ Built realistic bouncing with energy loss  \n",
        "✅ Managed multiple objects  \n",
        "✅ Added interactive spawning  \n",
        "\n",
        "### What's Coming Next?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Day 03: Pong Game** - We'll use our physics knowledge to create a classic two-player game with paddles and a ball!\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-important}\n",
        "## 📝 Homework (Optional)\n",
        "\n",
        "Before Day 03:\n",
        "1. Experiment with different friction and gravity values\n",
        "2. Try adding wind (constant horizontal acceleration)\n",
        "3. Create a \"pool table\" simulation with multiple balls\n",
        "4. Make balls change color when they bounce\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## � Complete Code - Ready to Copy!\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "Day 02: Bouncing Ball Physics - Complete Working Version\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "import pygame\n",
        "import sys\n",
        "import random\n",
        "\n",
        "pygame.init()\n",
        "\n",
        "WINDOW_WIDTH = 800\n",
        "WINDOW_HEIGHT = 600\n",
        "FPS = 60\n",
        "\n",
        "WHITE = (255, 255, 255)\n",
        "BLACK = (0, 0, 0)\n",
        "RED = (255, 100, 100)\n",
        "BLUE = (100, 150, 255)\n",
        "GREEN = (100, 255, 150)\n",
        "PURPLE = (200, 100, 255)\n",
        "YELLOW = (255, 255, 100)\n",
        "ORANGE = (255, 165, 100)\n",
        "\n",
        "COLORS = [RED, BLUE, GREEN, PURPLE, YELLOW, ORANGE]\n",
        "\n",
        "GRAVITY = 0.5\n",
        "FRICTION = 0.99\n",
        "MIN_BOUNCE_VELOCITY = 0.5\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "class Ball:\n",
        "    def __init__(self, x, y, radius, color):\n",
        "        self.x = x\n",
        "        self.y = y\n",
        "        self.radius = radius\n",
        "        self.color = color\n",
        "        self.vx = random.uniform(-10, 10)\n",
        "        self.vy = random.uniform(-15, -5)\n",
        "        \n",
        "    def update(self):\n",
        "        self.vy += GRAVITY\n",
        "        self.x += self.vx\n",
        "        self.y += self.vy\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if self.x - self.radius <= 0:\n",
        "            self.x = self.radius\n",
        "            self.vx = abs(self.vx) * FRICTION\n",
        "        elif self.x + self.radius >= WINDOW_WIDTH:\n",
        "            self.x = WINDOW_WIDTH - self.radius\n",
        "            self.vx = -abs(self.vx) * FRICTION\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if self.y + self.radius >= WINDOW_HEIGHT:\n",
        "            self.y = WINDOW_HEIGHT - self.radius\n",
        "            if abs(self.vy) > MIN_BOUNCE_VELOCITY:\n",
        "                self.vy = -abs(self.vy) * FRICTION\n",
        "            else:\n",
        "                self.vy = 0\n",
        "            self.vx *= 0.95\n",
        "        \n",
        "        if self.y - self.radius <= 0:\n",
        "            self.y = self.radius\n",
        "            self.vy = abs(self.vy) * FRICTION\n",
        "            \n",
        "    def draw(self, surface):\n",
        "        pygame.draw.circle(surface, self.color, (int(self.x), int(self.y)), self.radius)\n",
        "        end_x = int(self.x + self.vx * 3)\n",
        "        end_y = int(self.y + self.vy * 3)\n",
        "        pygame.draw.line(surface, WHITE, (int(self.x), int(self.y)), (end_x, end_y), 2)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def main():\n",
        "    screen = pygame.display.set_mode((WINDOW_WIDTH, WINDOW_HEIGHT))\n",
        "    pygame.display.set_caption(\"Day 02: Bouncing Ball Physics\")\n",
        "    clock = pygame.time.Clock()\n",
        "    \n",
        "    balls = []\n",
        "    for _ in range(5):\n",
        "        x = random.randint(50, WINDOW_WIDTH - 50)\n",
        "        y = random.randint(50, 200)\n",
        "        radius = random.randint(15, 40)\n",
        "        color = random.choice(COLORS)\n",
        "        balls.append(Ball(x, y, radius, color))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    font = pygame.font.Font(None, 36)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    running = True\n",
        "    while running:\n",
        "        for event in pygame.event.get():\n",
        "            if event.type == pygame.QUIT:\n",
        "                running = False\n",
        "            elif event.type == pygame.MOUSEBUTTONDOWN:\n",
        "                x, y = event.pos\n",
        "                radius = random.randint(15, 40)\n",
        "                color = random.choice(COLORS)\n",
        "                balls.append(Ball(x, y, radius, color))\n",
        "        \n",
        "        for ball in balls:\n",
        "            ball.update()\n",
        "        \n",
        "        screen.fill(BLACK)\n",
        "        for ball in balls:\n",
        "            ball.draw(screen)\n",
        "        \n",
        "        text = font.render(\"Click to add balls!\", True, WHITE)\n",
        "        screen.blit(text, (10, 10))\n",
        "        \n",
        "        pygame.display.flip()\n",
        "        clock.tick(FPS)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    pygame.quit()\n",
        "    sys.exit()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
        "    main()\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
